This is a new Saiga conversion on an IZ-105 20ga. with a 19" barrel.The FCG has been moved forward and a US Made FCG has been installed. We have re-profiled and polished this FCG to enhance the performance and reliability of the gun.This is a 4 port gun and we have done the necessary port work on the gas block and barrel to enable reliable performance with low brass ammo. A RAM Trigger Guard has been installed and a new New Hogue grip.A Tromix Oversize Charging Knob has been installed.
The trigger pull is approx 4.5 lbs. but we can lower it some more at minimal cost.
19" barrel.A UTG US Made Quad Rail System has been installed and comes with a longer top rail as well as the one installed on the gun if you wish to change it. It also includes 12 rail covers.A US Made Copy of a Bulgarian Brake has also been installed. An adjustable gas plug has been added as well to enhance gas control in the gun and it has been modified to enhance the port work that we have done inside the gas block. An Over Molded Hogue Grip was installed. A Mag Release extension was also added to facilitate operating the gun without taking your hand off of the pistol grip. Paint has been touched up with a solvent resistant Ceramic based paint.The rear tang has been removed and the rear of the receiver has been reshaped and an internal support block has been installed to support the ACE hardware.We remove the tang in order to not have to use external mounting blocks that extend the length of the gun. A Folding ACE Skeleton stock with a 1" butt pad was then installed along with the ACE Push Button folding hinge, the best in the business.
An after market recoil spring was also added to aid in reliability.Fire the gun, release a mag, lock open the bolt, all without taking your hand off the pistol grip. The gun handles flawlessly as all guns modified by our gunsmiths go to the range for testing with multiple rounds put through them before shipping.

A low numbered Rock Island 1903 Springfield, in .30-06.  

*Low Numbered* There are lots of tales of these firearms failing catastrophically, and many people are afraid to shoot them, shoot at your own risk.  That said, this rifle was made in 1917, and no Rock Island rifles produced that year suffered catastrophic failures.  

Rebarreled in 44,  Comes with original 1944 Boyt Leather sling, added to the firearm when the army ordinance corps. was trying to create a backup arsenal of rifles stateside.  Sling has some cracks, but has been stored well, and treated with Picard's antique leather care product.

title: For Sale:  Remington 552 SpeedMaster Semi Auto, short, Long  , LR
location: Wake forest, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
This Semi- automatic gun is chambered for 22 caliber shorts, longs and Long Rifle. The Model 552 is a direct descendant of the Remington 550 Design by Carbine Williams in North Carolina.  The Primary improvement is the addition of a Grooved Receiver that allows a scope mount, and new stock design. The 550's and 550-1's has roll engraving "Williams Patents" . The name of David "Carbine" Williams held the patent on the 550's "floating chamber" and had Remington include his name on the rifle. 
David Marshall Williams (November 13, 1900 – January 8, 1975) was the American firearms designer of the floating chamber and the short-stroke piston. Both designs used the high pressure gas generated in or near the breech of the firearm to operate the action of semi-automatic firearms like the M1 Carbine. Williams was instrumental in the design of the M1 Carbine used in WW2. Quite the genius in action design, he was played by Jimmy Stewart in a movie of the same name. 
This  gun is very good original condition, no rust on the bluing and very few light scratches on  the stock. The barrel is 24" long. The gun was made before 1968 when the Gun Control Act of 1968 was passed, requiring serial numbers. The gun functions flawlessly. 
I will ship this rifle, at buyers expense and in compliance with all applicable laws. If sold outside the Raleigh NC area, I require advanced payment by postal money order. More Photos available upon Request.
